# postgresql_grant_role (Resource)

The `postgresql_grant_role` resource creates and manages membership in a role to one or more other roles in a non-authoritative way.

When using `postgresql_grant_role` resource it is likely because the role you are modifying was created outside of this provider.

## Example Usage

```hcl
resource "postgresql_grant_role" "grant_root" {
  role              = "root"
  grant_role        = "application"
  with_admin_option = true
}
```

~> **Note:** If you use `postgresql_grant_role` for a role that you also manage with a `postgresql_role` resource, you need to ignore the changes of the `roles` attribute in the `postgresql_role` resource or they will fight over what your role grants should be:

```hcl
resource "postgresql_role" "bob" {
  name = "bob"

  lifecycle {
    ignore_changes = [
      roles,
    ]
  }
}

resource "postgresql_grant_role" "bob_admin" {
  role       = "bob"
  grant_role = "admin"
}
```

